	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.89]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>When I saw the auction for this in EC, two things crossed my mind.&nbsp;&nbsp;The first was how great it would be for my necro (10), who has a pitifully low charisma and could use the boost, and the second thing that occurred to me was how great it would be on the enchanter (37) that I was currently playing.  The 800pp price tag meant no love for the necro that day, but I'll blow that much for my enchanter anytime, especially on such a great item--never bothered to do a PC, had no idea it regularly sold for so much more.  This brought my int up to 190 (still no int from shoes, legs, hands, or waist).  You people seem to assume that whoever is going to use this actually looted it in chardok.  While I imagine there are a lot of people there that would use it, there are a lot more lower-level (i.e. not ready for chardok) players that could use it, too.  As for the whole class argument, who cares?  The stats cater to enchanters, but anybody that can wear it, is an int caster, and sells items can make use of the stats.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
