	   <tr><td colspan=2>While i do agree Enshrouded is a better mask, i'd also point out... a lot of people do chardock, less people do HS.<br><br>As for removing 'big' intel items, that's opposite of what needs to be done.&nbsp;&nbsp;You want to maintain items with large intel boosts.  The fewer slots you use to gain your 200, the more slots you have open for AC/Mana/HP items.  5 intel on an item isn't very large, and most people who can rumage around in chardok probably wouldn't notice the difference of it.<br><br>The thing that is nice about this mask is exact stats... there's no dex, or wisdom.. things that an intel doesn't really need (which in itself is amazing).  AC is nice, most things with more AC are much harder to get, and many of them will be "claimed" by other classes as the $9.95 they pay each month always seems to be more important than the $9.95 that intels pay. <br><br>At level 50+, whining about 3 intel really shouldn't even happen.  Even if you run 200, the odds are you're going to run out of Hp's before you run out of mana.<br>&nbsp;<br>Moraganth<br><br>Good brewer, better drunk</td></tr>
